## D-010 ‚Äî Tranche dependency order (within field-adaptation authority)
- **Choice:** A ‚Üí B ‚Üí C ‚Üí D ‚Üí E ‚Üí F ‚Üí G as per SRS. Within tranches:
  - A.1 ‚Üí A.2 ‚Üí A.3 ‚Üí A.4 (foundation infrastructure) before A.5 (metadata substrate which depends on A.2 gating)
  - A.6 + A.7 + A.8 can run in parallel after A.5
  - B record families load on top of A's storage
  - C requires A + B; runs Cedar Ridge engagement after both green
  - D.5 (comms_*) depends on D-005 (CENTRAL_MCP_TOKEN); D.4 (federation) depends on D.5 audit infrastructure; D.3 (dashboards) can land last
  - E (rollup) requires D's MCP tool consolidation
  - F (security) runs verification across all merged work
  - G (user stories + evals) is the proof tier ‚Äî runs against everything
- **Rationale:** Honors SRS-stated order while respecting actual dependency edges.

## D-011 ‚Äî MindsDB substitution policy
- **Question:** Stand up MindsDB sidecar or substitute?
- **Choice (provisional, will lock when reached):** Attempt MindsDB Coolify sidecar first; if image pull or schema bootstrap takes more than 30 minutes of work, fall back to a federation-MCP-native shim that exposes `federation.query.<scope>` tools dispatching to scoped MCP clients per source (VinSolutions, Google Analytics, Resend, etc.).
- **Rationale:** SRS 5.D.4 grants explicit room to choose differently with rationale. MindsDB is preferred for the SQL-across-heterogeneous-sources value; the shim covers the contract (auth + audit + scope) even without ML.
- **Reversal:** Swap engine; tool contract unchanged.

## D-012 ‚Äî Dashboard renderer substitution policy
- **Question:** Stand up Metabase sidecar or substitute?
- **Choice (provisional):** Attempt Metabase Coolify sidecar; if blocked, ship plugin-native renderer using existing React + recharts/visx pointing at MCP-exposed Brain queries. Per-profile JWT either way.
- **Rationale:** SRS 5.D.3 says Metabase is default candidate but Lightdash/Superset are acceptable. Plugin-native is an extension of that authority when sidecar provisioning is the blocker.
- **Reversal:** swap renderer; data path unchanged.

